    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom of the stems are turning this sickly yellow color but the top ones look okay. what's probably going on and how do i fix the soil?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like your tomato plants might be experiencing a case of \"bottom rot\" or \"lower stem rot,\" which is often caused by a lack of oxygen, poor drainage, or a fungal infection. To fix your soil, you should first ensure it's well-draining, which means you might need to add some organic matter like compost or perlite. Consider raising your plants a bit higher or providing a small layer of gravel at the bottom of the pots to improve drainage. Additionally, make sure to water your plants at the base rather than from above to avoid wetting the leaves and spreading any potential fungal issues. If the problem persists, you may need to treat the affected plants with a fungicide. Remember to always check the soil moisture before watering, and keep an eye out for signs of disease. Happy gardening!",
      "source": "target",
